title: GlusterFS monitoring

agents: glusterfs

description:
 Monitors GlusterFS cluster and volumes.

 This check creates:
  - One service for cluster health (peers)
  - One service per volume

item:
 Name of the Gluster volume.

inventory:
 One service is created per detected GlusterFS volume.

parameters:
 brick_down_warn:
  Number of bricks that must be down before a warning is triggered.

 brick_down_crit:
  Number of bricks that must be down before a critical state is triggered.

 warn_on_heal:
  If enabled, the service enters WARNING when heal activity is detected.

levels:
 OK:
  All peers connected and no bricks are down.

 WARNING:
  - Number of down bricks >= brick_down_warn
  - OR heal activity detected

 CRITICAL:
  - Number of down bricks >= brick_down_crit
  - OR peer disconnected